      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Frances Hodgson Burnett (1849-1924) was a British-American author.  She wrote plays and novels, but is best known for her children's books <emph render="italic">Little Lord Fauntleroy</emph> (1886), <emph render="italic">A Little Princess</emph> (1905), and <emph render="italic">The Secret Garden</emph> (1911).</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Frances Hodgson Burnett Letter</emph> consists of a single short letter from the English author to a Mrs. Edward Lawrence White, thanking her for sending some books.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
